 the 24 top players seeded for the tournament will square up against the Indian star on table one today. The Nigerian is ranked 21st in the world while the 28-year-old Indian star is rated 37th while both players will be meeting at the level for the first time with odds favouring the Nigerian. Vanguard News Nigeria As the only African to make it to the quater-final of the World Cup and Olympic Games, the International Table Tennis Federation (ITTF) through it Publication Editor, Ian Marshal has described Aruna Quadri has a record setter following his feat at the Polish Open at the weekend. October 10, 2017 In "News" The draws for the International Table Tennis Federation (ITTF) World Tour, Lagos Open hold today as 12-man Egyptian contingent arrive in Lagos. March 9, 2015 In "Sports" From the knockout draw conducted on Saturday, August 3, number one seed, Aruna Quadri of Nigeria may slug it out against Egypt’s Omar Assar in the semifinal of the men’s singles at the 2019 ITTF Africa Cup holding at the Molade Okoya-Thomas Hall of Teslim Balogun Stadium. August 5, 2019 In "News"